main event: A silver, round object was observed in the sky for approximately 1 minute.
interesting points: The object was the size of a jet aircraft at a distance of 7 or 8 miles.
The object had no apparent aerodynamic features such as wings, tail or any means of control.
The object moved at extreme speed in jet magnitudes.
The object disappeared into a cloud bank.
The observation was made from the ground at an altitude of 22,000 feet with a high wind airspeed of 39 mph.
location: Approximately 12 miles east of Trenton Air Force Base
